  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_4' aria-label=\" Rupa and Co. Limited and Another versus Firhad Hakim and Others pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('4','2025','2025_2_648_656','2025INSC245'); ><font size='4'> <strong>RUPA AND CO. LIMITED AND ANOTHER<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>FIRHAD HAKIM AND OTHERS </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 2 S.C.R. 648</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 245</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010001512025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : BHUSHAN RAMKRISHNA GAVAI<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, AUGUSTINE GEORGE MASIH</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the High Court having, on earlier occasions, emphasized the necessity to abide by the command of its directions and also issuing notice to the Chief Secretary to comply with the order, was justified in directing the parties Non-compliance of the order of the High Court &ndash; Aggravated contempt &ndash; HIDCO agreed to convey land to the appellants on freehold basis for Rs. 4,00,92,000/- &ndash; Appellant paid the entire amount &ndash; However, HIDCO decided that allotment would not be on freehold basis but on<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 11-02-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 2376/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Directions issued</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('4','2025','2025_2_648_656','2025INSC245','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-